summary: The season finale of the "The Acolyte" has drawn mixed reactions from critics. While some praised the cameos and surprises in the episode, others found it disappointing and anticlimactic. Forbes criticized the episode as "dreadful," while Den of Geek and Star Wars News Net highlighted the unexpected twists. IGN and Midwest Film Journal offered more balanced reviews, acknowledging both the strengths and weaknesses of the episode. However, Dork Side of the Force and Vulture were more critical, describing the ending as "hopeless" and "an uneven series." Pajiba highlighted a particular scene featuring a Jedi and a mysterious character in a cave, but failed to provide a clear verdict on the episode. Filmstories agreed with the overall disappointment, calling the finale "anticlimactic." Kotaku's review of the previous episode, Episode 7, focused on the consequences of misunderstandings within the story.
